list.item:
Support for the position of Cuba, which has refused to join the
                            treaty, asserting that U.S. nuclear weapons remain in Puerto Rico, the
                            Canal Zone and “and other Latin American areas”;

The fact that the Treaty contains no ban on the transportation of
                            nuclear weapons and that the United States has refused to stop sending
                            nuclear-armed vessels through the Panama Canal;

The position taken by Brazil, with which the Soviet Union disagrees as
                            we do, with respect to the Treaty’s provisions on peaceful nuclear
                            explosions;

The Treaty will supplement our national efforts to detect any
                            introduction of nuclear weapons into the region by the Soviet Union;
                            and
